## Design Decisions (from brainstorm)

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Schema depth | Top-level only | Craft only reads dates/course/breaks/deployment |
| Normalize order | Before apply_defaults() | So defaults and validation work on canonical schema |
| Field mapping | name→number, full_name→title, capitalize semester | Full compatibility with stat-545 |
| Break validation | Allow start == end | Single-day breaks (MLK Day) are valid |
| Conflict rule | Merge (semester_info fills gaps) | Non-destructive — craft-native keys win |
| Deploy normalization | Yes (branches→deployment) | stat-545 uses branches.production/draft |
| Error messages | Silent | Flow-cli owns the schema; craft is the adapter |
| Test fixture | Hardcoded in test file | Self-contained, works without stat-545 repo |
| Docs location | Guide only (not CLAUDE.md) | CLAUDE.md already over 150-line budget |
| semester_progress.py | No changes needed | Reads normalized config downstream |

## Step 1: Normalize Config (`teach_config.py`)

**File:** `commands/utils/teach_config.py`

Add `_normalize_config(raw: dict) -> dict`:
- [ ] Course: `course.name` → `course.number` (if number missing)
- [ ] Course: `course.full_name` → `course.title` (if title missing)
- [ ] Course: `course.semester` capitalize (spring → Spring)
- [ ] Dates: `semester_info.start_date` → `dates.start` (if dates.start missing)
- [ ] Dates: `semester_info.end_date` → `dates.end` (if dates.end missing)
- [ ] Dates: `semester_info.breaks` → `dates.breaks` (if dates.breaks missing)
- [ ] Deploy: `branches.production` → `deployment.production_branch` (if missing)
- [ ] Deploy: `branches.draft` → `deployment.draft_branch` (if missing)

**Design:** Non-destructive, idempotent, silent. Uses `setdefault()` pattern.
Only fills gaps — never overwrites existing craft-native keys.
Original flow-cli keys stay in dict (other tools may read them).

**Call site:** Insert `config = _normalize_config(config)` in `load_teach_config()`
between YAML parse and `apply_defaults()`.

